</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FEBB0CFCAD00FFADFF28ADB5FB915AA4" box="[197,1151,693,719]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="B61E5F77AD00FFADFF28ADB5FB915AA4" blockId="15.[151,1436,152,1111]" box="[197,1151,693,719]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="84D58365AD00FFADFF28ADB5FEC05AA4" bold="true" box="[197,302,693,719]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Ecology.</emphasis>
A bathyal species associated with sediments of canyons and seamounts.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FEBB0CFCAD00FFADFF28ADDBFEAB5C3C" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="B61E5F77AD00FFADFF28ADDBFEAB5C3C" blockId="15.[151,1436,152,1111]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis id="84D58365AD00FFADFF28ADDBFED05A9E" bold="true" box="[197,318,731,757]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks.</emphasis>
The flange on the uropod 2 peduncle of this species is a highly diagnostic character that seems to be shared only by a small number of other 
<taxonomicName id="71A124F4AD00FFADFD3EAC02FC385B77" box="[723,982,770,796]" class="Malacostraca" family="Tryphosidae" genus="Hippomedon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="84D58365AD00FFADFD3EAC02FC9F5B70" box="[723,881,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Hippomedon</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, all of which are found only in 
<collectingCountry id="CEB61FE7AD00FFADFA8EAC02FF165B28" name="New Zealand" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
waters. Of those, 
<taxonomicName id="71A124F4AD00FFADFE31AC29FCB95B28" authority="K. H. Barnard, 1930" authorityName="K. H. Barnard" authorityYear="1930" box="[476,855,809,835]" class="Malacostraca" family="Tryphosidae" genus="Hippomedon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incisus">
<emphasis id="84D58365AD00FFADFE31AC29FDB95B29" box="[476,599,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">H. incisus</emphasis>
K.H. Barnard, 1930
</taxonomicName>
, differs from the present species by the incised posterodistal corner of epimeron 3 at the base of the spine, and the presence of eyes. 
<taxonomicName id="71A124F4AD00FFADFB70AC50FE2B5BFB" authority="Lowry &amp; Stoddart, 1983" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Stoddart" authorityYear="1983" class="Malacostraca" family="Tryphosidae" genus="Hippomedon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manene">
<emphasis id="84D58365AD00FFADFB70AC50FA755B02" box="[1181,1435,848,873]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Hippomedon manene</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D2302286AD00FFADFF7AAC76FE2B5BFB" author="Lowry, J. K. &amp; Stoddart, H. E." box="[151,453,886,912]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="279 - 294" refId="ref9650" refString="Lowry, J. K. &amp; Stoddart, H. E. (1983) The shallow-water gammaridean Amphipoda of the subantarctic islands of New Zealand and Australia (Lysianassoidea). Journal of the Royal Society of New Zealand, 13 (4), 279 - 294." type="journal article" year="1983">Lowry &amp; Stoddart, 1983</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is also quite similar, but lacks the posterior lobe on the gnathopod 2 carpus, the excavate posterior margin of pereopod 7, and the small up-turned spine on the anterodistal corner of epimeron 1. 
<taxonomicName id="71A124F4AD00FFADFF58ACC4FDB35BB5" authority="Fenwick, 1983" authorityName="Fenwick" authorityYear="1983" box="[181,605,964,990]" class="Malacostraca" family="Tryphosidae" genus="Hippomedon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="whero">
<emphasis id="84D58365AD00FFADFF58ACC4FE4E5BB6" box="[181,416,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Hippomedon whero</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="D2302286AD00FFADFE44ACC4FDB35BB5" author="Fenwick, G. D." box="[425,605,964,990]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="133 - 146" refId="ref9503" refString="Fenwick, G. D. (1983) Two new sand-dwelling amphipods from Kaikoura, New Zealand (Oedicerotidae and Lysianassidae). New Zealand Journal of Zoology, 10, 133 - 146." type="journal article" year="1983">Fenwick, 1983</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, differs from 
<taxonomicName id="71A124F4AD00FFADFCEEACC4FC9C5BB6" authorityName="Kilgallen" authorityYear="2009" box="[771,882,964,989]" class="Malacostraca" family="Tryphosidae" genus="Hippomedon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iugum">
<emphasis id="84D58365AD00FFADFCEEACC4FC9C5BB6" box="[771,882,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">H. iugum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape of both the lateral cephalic lobes and the 1 
<superScript id="41D4F23FAD00FFADFEE9ACEAFEE15B93" attach="left" box="[260,271,1002,1016]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">st</superScript>
urosomite. Finally, both 
<taxonomicName id="71A124F4AD00FFADFDD5ACEEFD565C6C" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Stoddart" authorityYear="1983" box="[568,696,1006,1031]" class="Malacostraca" family="Tryphosidae" genus="Hippomedon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manene">
<emphasis id="84D58365AD00FFADFDD5ACEEFD565C6C" box="[568,696,1006,1031]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">H. manene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="71A124F4AD00FFADFD1EACEEFCB15C6C" authorityName="Fenwick" authorityYear="1983" box="[755,863,1006,1031]" class="Malacostraca" family="Tryphosidae" genus="Hippomedon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="whero">
<emphasis id="84D58365AD00FFADFD1EACEEFCB15C6C" box="[755,863,1006,1031]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">H. whero</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have eyes with crystalline lenses, and the males of those species exhibit one large, over-developed calceolus on the 1 
<superScript id="41D4F23FAD00FFADFC20AB14FC365C49" attach="left" box="[973,984,1044,1058]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">st</superScript>
flagellar article which is absent in 
<taxonomicName id="71A124F4AD00FFADFA92AB17FF0E5C3C" authority="Kilgallen, 2009" authorityName="Kilgallen" authorityYear="2009" class="Malacostraca" family="Tryphosidae" genus="Hippomedon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iugum" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="84D58365AD00FFADFA92AB17FF0E5C3C" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">H. iugum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="84D58365AD00FFADFF0AAB3DFEAB5C3C" bold="true" box="[231,325,1085,1111]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9FE63E1EAD00FFADFF0AAB3DFEAB5C3C" box="[231,325,1085,1111]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
